# Three-dimensional plots
Most examples were adapted from the official pages of [Wolfram Language Documentation Center](https://reference.wolfram.com/language/).

<br/>

## Spherical Plot
An example of $Y_{2,0}$

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Display: markdown
Type: Output
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
# Three-dimensional plots
Most examples were adapted from the official pages of [Wolfram Language Documentation Center](https://reference.wolfram.com/language/).

<br />

## Spherical Plot
An example of $Y_{2,0}$

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Props:
  Hidden: false
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
(*SbB[*)Subscript[Y(*|*),(*|*)k_,q_](*]SbB*)[\[Theta]_, \[Phi]_] := SphericalHarmonicY[k,q, \[Theta], \[Phi]]

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Props:
  Hidden: false
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
SphericalPlot3D[(*SbB[*)Subscript[Y(*|*),(*|*)4,0](*]SbB*)[\[Theta], \[Phi]], {\[Theta],0,\[Pi]}, {\[Phi],0,2\[Pi]}]

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Output
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
